commit.message:
OSESMO Option S

Customized version of OSESMO capable of handling PG&E Option S rate, which features both daily and monthly demand charges. Requires slightly-modified retail-rate data format, which is also included here.

Intentation Fix

Fixed issue where line was improperly indented.

Fix to Equivalent Cycling Constraint

All cycling must occur before the "padding" days at the end of each month, which are removed after optimization. Fixes bug where number of annual cycles was below Equivalent_Cycling_Constraint_Input.

LADWP A-2B (OLD) Modeling

Added LADWP A-2B (OLD) rate and performed modeling for all C&I projects previously mapped to SCE rates.

PG&E E-TOU-C (NEW) and SCE TOU-D-4-9PM (NEW) Modeling

Added PG&E E-TOU-C (NEW) and SCE TOU-D-4-9PM (NEW) rates for additional residential rate modeling.

Updates to OSESMO Optimization Algorithm Outline

Minor corrections to OSESMO Optimization Algorithm Outline.

Folder Name Change

Change subfolder name from "MATLAB Code" to "OSESMO MATLAB"

LADWP R-1B (OLD) Modeling with LADWP Emissions Evaluation Signal

New inputs and evaluation-signal-mapping logic for LADWP R-1B (OLD) modeling with LADWP emissions evaluations ignal.

LADWP R-1B (OLD) Modeling

Added LADWP R-1B (OLD) rate and performed modeling for all residential cases.

OSESMO Python 1.0

The OSESMO Python translation effort is now complete! Translated Monthly Emissions Impact plot code. Added Retail Rate Master Index & Effective Date. Debugged & ran as function from Model_Input_Single_Run script. Performed comparison with results for OSESMO MATLAB to ensure equivalent outputs.

OSESMO Python v0.9 (WIP)

Further translation - save inputs/outputs and storage dispatch as array, convert to dataframe, write as csv.

OSESMO Python v0.8 (WIP) + OSESMO MATLAB Grid Cost Baseline Plot Name Fix

Additional OSESMO Python translation - plots & output reporting. Fixed misnamed filename for Grid Cost Baseline plot.

Model Runtime Fix

Fixed error where time components would appear as ":010" instead of ":10".

OSESMO MATLAB - PG&E E-6 (NEW) Analysis

Added PG&E E-6 (NEW) rate, iterated through all residential modeling cases with new rate.

OSESMO Python v0.7 (Work In Progress)

Fixed monthly concatenation, translated most plotting code.

OSESMO Python v0.6/Winter Coincident Peak DC Fix

Further development on OSESMO Python. Change to Winter Coincident Peak calculation in bill calculator - no longer assumes that demand charge is $0/kW.

OSESMO Python v0.5 (Work In Progress)

Functions to import data are complete. Optimization code is nearly done, but has not been tested. Code for calculating outputs and plotting data is not yet translated.

Work Paper

Added SGIP GHG Working Group Work Paper to repository.

Rerun Calibration Runs, Modify Energy Level Between Months

Rerun calibration runs, fix updating of Energy Levels between months (next month initial energy level should not equal current month final energy level if charging/discharging in last timestep of month.

PV Rounding, Utility Costs

Added rounding of PV sizes to nearest 0.1 kW, added calculation and plotting of utility costs, load profile/retail rate/PV profile master indices, improvements to plot axes
OSESMO Python 1.0

Repository Structure Changes, Sample Data

Put all MATLAB code in single folder, created new Python Code folder for translated files. Changed Sample Data folder so that filepaths were same as on Box drive, allowing users to easily run model using only the sample data in the Git repo. Minor change to monthly cost/savings plot legend label for clarity.

Added Sample Data

Added Sample Data - EnerNOC SF Office Load Profile, CSI PG&E C&I Solar PV Profile, PG&E E-19S OLD Rates Vectors, NP15 Emissions Data

Added Model Iteration Files + Minor Updates

Added scripts for iterating through residential and C&I (commercial and industrial) load profiles and rates.

Fixed bug in filepath to EnerNOC San Diego load data. Fixes to monthly costs graph to show negative values.

Add optimization algorithm outline documentation

Add optimization algorithm outline documentation.

Added Solar + Storage, Non-Economic Self-Consumption, Iteration Scripts, Functionalized Code

Added Solar + Storage functionality.
Added non-economic self-consumption mode.
Created scripts to iterate through specific combinations of model inputs.
Functionalized code for cost calculation and data import.

Added logo to README

Added logo to README

commit.message:
Storage Only V2

Version 2 of the Storage-Only Model. Modified to accept many new retail tariffs and tariff types, including those with no noncoincident, coincident peak, or coincident part-peak demand  charges, as well as per-day and per-month fixed charges. Added Equivalent Cycling Constraint and SGIP RTE Constraint. Added WattTime Public Model Forecasted Emissions Signal. Added new Load Profile Data sources.

Storage Only V1

Version 1 of the Storage Only model and the Inputs and Iteration script.
